            "body": "Sorry for the late answer, but I was still getting the same error after the fix, but I wanted to find out what was wrong and in my case it was somehow `nvim-tree` fault. \r\nThere was something in `nvim-tree` that was slowing down the nvim instance when the filesystem changed (when e.g. running `npm install` that changed node_modules folder and its contents).\r\nAfter migrating to the `neotree` for file explorer the hanging stopped appearing in the editor. \r\nWriting in case someone else happens to stumble upon the same problem",
